# Design System Domino Chain — Android

Always use design system resources for Android layouts and views. Do not hardcode colors, dimensions, or styles.

## Reference

See `docs/DESIGN_SYSTEM.md` for the full spec.

## Colors

Use named colors: `@color/ds_bg`, `@color/ds_text`, `@color/ds_text_muted`, `@color/ds_magenta`, `@color/ds_blue`, `@color/ds_violet`, etc. Never hardcode hex values in layouts.

Notes:
- Legacy aliases `@color/ds_amber` and `@color/ds_teal` still exist for compatibility.
- For new code, prefer explicit tokens (`ds_magenta`, `ds_blue`, `ds_violet`).

## Spacing

Use `@dimen/ds_space_xs` through `@dimen/ds_space_3xl`, and `@dimen/ds_page_padding`. Never hardcode `dp` values.

## Styles

- **Title**: `@style/DsTitle` or `DsTitleSmall`
- **Subtitle / labels**: `@style/DsSmall` or `DsSectionTitle`
- **Body**: `@style/DsBody`
- **Primary button**: `@style/DsButton`
- **Secondary button**: `@style/DsButtonSecondary`
- **Ghost button**: `@style/DsButtonGhost`
- **Input**: `@style/DsEditText`
- **Card**: `@drawable/ds_card_background`
- **Activation controls** (Switch/Checkbox/Radio): follow Material theme with DS `colorSecondary` (magenta).

## Android Branding (launcher + notification)

- Use official DS resources for app/notification icons:
  - `@mipmap/ic_launcher`, `@mipmap/ic_launcher_round`
  - `@drawable/ic_notification`
  - `@color/ic_launcher_background`
- Do not reintroduce custom launcher/notification assets outside DS-aligned `mipmap-*` / `drawable-*` folders.

## Layout Structure

```xml
<!-- Page with padding -->
android:padding="@dimen/ds_page_padding"
android:background="@color/ds_bg"

<!-- Card / block -->
android:background="@drawable/ds_card_background"
android:padding="@dimen/ds_space_lg"
```

